<h1>Skytrails Project Information</h1>

<h4>About the project</h4>
<a href="https://www.skytrails.org/">Skytrails</a> is a research prototype developed by Kenny Peng (klp98@cornell.edu), Sophie Greenwood, Erica Chiang, Jon Kleinberg, and Nikhil Garg. The project aims to explore how alternative interfaces can enable human agency and exploration of social media.

<h4>Research and Data Collection</h4>
By entering the website, you consent to having your usage of the website recorded. This data will be stored anonymously and is only accessible to our research team. We will only publish aggregate usage statistics.

<h4>Risks and discomforts</h4>
Since the posts come directly from the Bluesky platform, you may encounter posts that are discomforting or offensive. Posts are filtered to not include explicit adult content according to Bluesky’s labels, but there may remain not-safe-for-work content. No media (images or video) are displayed. You may leave the website at any time.

<h4>Benefits</h4>
You may benefit from the website by exploring the world of Bluesky content, potentially finding new areas of interest. 

